About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Did I expect this bag to hold up, nope. When my child said it wasn't a vacation with out a rolling suitcase and backpacks were just carrying your junk from place to place, I gave in and got her this bag. I fully expect I was going to be balancing it on my head as we traveled though 9 countries in under 3 weeks on and off trains, planes and long walks across cobble roads. To my surprise this was the little bag that could. We stacked backpacks food bags and weighed down this little wheelie case and it just kept on going. Much to my surprise this bag held up to heavy abuse we put it though and is ready to keep traveling. Also unique design made it easy to pick out of all the other bags when checked it easily fit on the planes and into the overhead bins of even the tiny planes.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great carry on! Recommend. Smooth rolling.
reviews.reviewText: Just got this carry-on and it is great. Super easy smooth rolling, great storage room, zippers are great so far. The handle is sturdy and smooth. It’s super light weight so it won’t add to weight.Wish it was expandable but it’s still gots lots of room.Only real negative is the protective plastic film they put on it for shipping … ugh you can’t get it all off!! It’s stuck on in The handle and along the edges and where the wheels are attached. You’ll need to take tweezers and pick at removing all the plastic to try and remove.But so far super great carry on.Wheels roll through parking garage with ease. Even over the bumps and divots in the garage. Goes over bumps and carpet easily and just keeps rolling. Very easy to push through isle of airplane too.Highly recommend. Will be buying another.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Defective, returned merchandise resold as new -- DO NOT BUY
reviews.reviewText: We bought 2 of these suitcases for our kids (ages 6 and 8) for Christmas; we chose this model because it is lightweight, has spinner wheels, has distinctive patterned exteriors that our kids think is fun, is still of a decent size, and has multiple handle positions that can adjust to be easily pulled by both kids and adults. When we opened the first suitcase, we found that the manufacturers tag was not attached and was simply lying loose in the box. We also noticed that the plastic protective coating that is supposed to be removed after purchase was already removed in all but a few places. When we opened the case, we found that one of the straps that are supposed to hold the clothes in the side of the case was not properly attached (this strap is critical because the suitcase is a 'clamshell' style, opening in the middle with 2 equal halves to fill with clothes rather than opening on an end -- without the strap, the clothes simply fall out when the suitcase is opened). Clearly this case had been purchased by someone else, returned as defective, and simply put back in a box and resold as new. We then opened the second suitcase; it had the plastic protective coating half-removed and one of the manufacturers' tags removed and lying loose in the box. When we tried to use the suitcase, we found that the handle was loose and wiggly, and would not lock in the lower position, which is exactly the position needed to pull the suitcase by an 8-year old. Thus, out of 2 suitcases with different patterns, both had been returned as defective and resold as new. Thus, both of these suitcases are being returned -- again. This is too bad: the rest of the suitcase seems to be of excellent construction and would have fit the bill perfectly. It's a shame that this sleazy retailer elected to resell defective merchandise as new, ruining what otherwise would have been a good product and a good purchasing experience.
